The idea is simple, for given n, we first find a palindrom p greater than n, then we check whether it's prime, if it's a prime, we get the result, otherwise, we find next palindrome greater than p

for example
```python
n = 723
then it will iterately generate following palindromes until getting one prime palindrome
747   # first palindrome greater than n
757 # second palindrome greater than n, and this is also a prime number
```
