**Thoughts and Intuition:**

When I first read this problem, I thought there's no way I can check every possible combination without TLE.  So I started looking for a pattern for a potential math solution.  I first noticed example 1 results in `true` with prime numbers `5` and `7` as input, and example 3 results in `false` with non-prime numbers `3` and `6` as input.  However, example 2 results in `true` with non-prime numbers also.  So I thought maybe GCD would work, and indeed it did!  After I solved this problem, I read about [Bezout's Identity in this post](https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-it-is-a-good-array/discuss/419324/Bezout's-Identity).

---

