Let a[] be the array of values and b[] be the array of constants such that
sigma( a[i]*b[i] ) =1 for 0 <= i < n.

This is equivalent to solving gcd( a[0], a[1] )*Y + sigma( a[i]*b[i]) = 1 for 2 <= i < n for some constant Y.

We simply reduced the problem from N to N-1. You can apply this recursively to solve the problem.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean isGoodArray(int[] a) {
        int ans=a[0];
        for(int t : a){
            if(ans==1) break;
            ans = gcd(ans, t);
        }
        return ans==1 ? true: false;
    }

    private int gcd( int a, int b) {
        if( a < b) return gcd(b,a);
        if( b == 0 ) return a;
        return gcd(b,a%b);
    }
}
```

