Additive property: if a==f (mod d), b==f (mod d), then it must be true that (x*a + y*b)==f (mod d)

So when we think of (x*a + y*b) mod d, and set the f ==0, then, there must be k=[1...d-1] ranges, which can map (x*a + y*b)/k to this range. Thus there must be a (x'*a + y'*b)==1 always existed. 


