So, something that I was able to deduce from the testcases was the prevalance of prime numbers in the solution array. And an array of composite numbers will automatically yield a 'false' output.
Proof-  Input array- [a,b]. Let's assume a and b are composite in nature
			therefore a=GCD*x and b=GCD*y
			sum= m*a + n*b = m*GCD*x + n*GCD*y = GCD(m*x + n*y)
			The only way sum=1 is if GCD=1 (and m*x + n*y=1). Else sum=0 or some other value.
			***This contradicts our assumption of a and b being composite is nature, hence they must be prime i.e GCD=1***


