solutions.content:
Basically, 1 can be achieved if the numbers do not have common divisors, so their greatest common divisor must be 1. C++ gives an inbuilt function to find gcd, but for java we gotta do it ourselves.
```
class Solution {
    public boolean isGoodArray(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length == 1 && nums[0] == 1)
            return true;

        int gcd = nums[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int a = (nums[i] > gcd) ? nums[i] : gcd;
            int b = (nums[i] < gcd) ? nums[i] : gcd;
            int r = b;
            while (a % b != 0) {
                r = a % b;
                a = b;
                b = r;
            }

            gcd = r;
            if (gcd == 1) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}
```

