# Observation 
(1) Boxes must be handled in order from left to right, this is a signal to use DP.
(2) Since it is 10^5. DP must be 1-dimension, i.e, for every index i we need to find a single index j and apply DP[i] = f(DP[j]) for some DP function f.

Intution ->
We can take as many boxes as possible using greedy approach.
But in one case,
the last several small boxes in this trip,
are going to the same port as the first box in the next trips.
We may probably let it go in the next trip,
we waste a little weight, but we can save a trip.


# Approach

First we added the box at position i. Then we remove boxes at the starting poistion of ship based on following rules:

The shipload must be within max weight and max count of the boxes.
Make room for more boxes as long as the result at current position trips[i+1] won't change. (This is greedy solution)
The cases:

base case: for 1 box, we need 2 trips for one shipload to deliver it and return.
general case: for 2 or more boxes case, adding one shipload would result in 2 trips + diff ports.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

# Conclusion 

There are many ways to solve this problem. I felt sliding window is the simplest of all. But,someone may have contrasting view point. So,try other approaches and go for approach which comforts you the best. 

