1. The shipload must be within max weight and max count of the boxes.
2. Make room for more boxes as long as the result at current position trips[i+1] won't change. (This is greedy solution)

The cases: 
1. base case: for 1 box, we need 2 trips for one shipload to deliver it and return.
2. general case: for 2 or more boxes case, adding one shipload would result in 2 trips + diff ports.

Why 2 trips? because the ship needs to return and come back at **this** same port at position "start".


