This is a difficult problem. The O(n^2) DP solution is rather easy to come up with, but it will get TLE. It however helped me with coming up a `O(N)` solution, so let's look at the code first.

For each index `i`, we search backwards and treat `j ... i` as a group. The cost would be `cost + dp[j-1]` for all valid `j`. 

#### TLE at Last 4 Test Cases
```Java
// class Solution {
//     public int boxDelivering(int[][] boxes, int portsCount, int maxBoxes, int maxWeight) {
//         int n = boxes.length, INF = (int)1e9;
