//         Arrays.fill(dp, INF);
//         dp[0]=2;
//         for (int i = 1 ; i<n; i++){
//             for (int j = i, w = 0, cur = 0; j >= 0; j--){
//                 w+=boxes[j][1];
//                 if (j==i||boxes[j][0]!=boxes[j+1][0]){
//                     cur++;
//                 }
//                 if (w <= maxWeight && cur <= maxBoxes){
//                     dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], 1 + cur + (j==0?0:dp[j-1]));
//                 }else{
//                     break;
//                 }
//             }
//         }
//         return dp[n-1];
//     }
// }
```
so how do we optimize this into `O(n)`? 
This looks awfully like a mono queue to me. Because we want the minimum `DP[j] + cost form j+1 to i` from the subarray `j ... i`.
So we should be able to do that with a mono queue.
We must put the **adjusted** value into the mono queue, not `dp[i]`for it to work properly.
Then, we will get the min result from the TLE solution for each `dp[i]` in O(1).

#### We Need
1. Index and adjusted weight inside the mono queue
2. A prefix weight array (long type) to check weight requirement
3. A diff array to compute the additional cost incurred by different type of parcels

#### Edge Case
There is one that took me a while to debug:
`diff[deque.peekFirst()[0]+1]`
We must `+1` here. Consider 2 adjacent boxes . If the previous box is picked, the diff pointer should be at `i+1`, not `i`. Otherwise we will count extra. 
#### Java
```Java
// Time Complexity: O(n)
// Space Complexity: O(n)
class Solution {
    public int boxDelivering(int[][] boxes, int portsCount, int maxBoxes, int maxWeight) {
        int n = boxes.length, INF = (int)1e9;
        int[] dp = new int[n+1];
        Arrays.fill(dp, INF);
        dp[0]=0;
        Deque<int[]> deque = new ArrayDeque<>();
        long[] pre = new long[n+1];
        int[] diff= new int[n+1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++){ // prefix sum for weight 
            pre[i]=boxes[i-1][1]+pre[i-1];
        }
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++){ // additional cost
            diff[i]=boxes[i-1][0]==boxes[i-2][0]?diff[i-1]:diff[i-1]+1;
        }
        deque.offer(new int[]{0, 0}); // base case 
        for (int i = 1 ; i<=n; i++){
            while(i - deque.peekFirst()[0] > maxBoxes || pre[i] - pre[deque.peekFirst()[0]] > maxWeight){ // invalid, remove it
                deque.pollFirst();
            }
            dp[i]=diff[i]-diff[deque.peekFirst()[0]+1]+dp[deque.peekFirst()[0]]+2; // dp value
            int cur = dp[i] - diff[i==n?0:i+1];
            while(!deque.isEmpty() && cur < deque.peekLast()[1]){ // purge based on adjusted value, NOT dp value
                deque.pollLast();
            }
            deque.offerLast(new int[]{i, cur}); // put adjusted value into the mono queue.
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

