solutions.content:
**Intuition :** 

* Idea is to store count of all points lying on x-axis with x-coordinate as point[0]. And for each point on x-axis, we have corresponding y-coordinate. 

		x_axis[x][y] = count of points with coordinate {x,y}. 

* Now, for check, we need to pick all points lying on x = point[0]. For all such we calculate side length and find remaining two points at same distance on left and right side of x = point[0] (+-) side_length. 


		-> p1 = { x, y }    # This is given as input
		-> p2 = { x, y' }   # We pick all the points p2 with x_coordinate = x  
		* Thus side_length = abs(y - y')

		// We find all valid p3 and p4 lying on both sides of p1 and p2 along x & y axis

		// Square on right side of p1 & p2 with line x acting as mirror
		-> p3' = { x + side_length , y }
		-> p4' = { x + side_length , y' }

		// Square on left side of p1 & p2 with line x acting as mirror
		-> p3'' = { x - side_length , y }
		-> p4'' = { x - side_length , y' }

		Note : y' (p2) can lie anywhere, above or below p1(y). But that does not effect our calculations.


![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/424ef955-ea4b-4e02-8db3-636e509bed91_1632053370.123253.png)



* Now, to get count we need to multiply count of all possible p2, p3, and p4 possible points.

		count of right side squares = count(p2) * count(p4') * count(p3')
		count of left side squares = count(p2) * count(p4'') * count(p3'')

		=> result = (count of left side squares + count of right side squares)
# Code:
```
class DetectSquares {
public:
    vector<unordered_map<int, int>> x_axis;

    DetectSquares() {
        x_axis = vector<unordered_map<int, int>>(1005);
    }

    void add(vector<int> point) {
        int x = point[0];
        int y = point[1];
        x_axis[x][y]++;
    }

    int count(vector<int> point) {
        int x = point[0], y = point[1];
        int res = 0;
        for (auto& it : x_axis[x]) {                // For all points lying on x_axis with value x_coordinate = x
            int y_coord = it.first;
            int countOcc = it.second;

            if (y == y_coord) continue;
            int sideLength = abs(y_coord - y);

			 // counting for p3' and p4'
            if (x + sideLength <= 1000)    // x_coordinate should be within range [0, 1000]
            {
                int newX = x + sideLength;
                res += x_axis[x][y_coord] * x_axis[newX][y_coord] * x_axis[newX][y];
            }

			// counting for p3'' and p4''
            if (x - sideLength >= 0)       // x_coordinate should be within range [0, 1000]
            {
                int newX = x - sideLength;
                res += x_axis[x][y_coord] * x_axis[newX][y_coord] * x_axis[newX][y];
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

**Time :**
* **add() : O(1)**
* **count() : O(n)**

**Space : O(n)**

