# Intuition
It's comfortable to use HashMap to store <Point, int> values where int - number of points with the same x and y, Point - simple class with  fields x and y. Also, we need to define equals() and hashCode() to store points properly in the Map.

# Approach
add() method:
 - we add point to hashmap and update count.

count() method:
 - we go through all points from the hashmap and check 2 moments:
      1. They have equal distnace between x and y coordinates to make diagonal of square.
      2. They are not equal because we are allowed to count squares only with positive area.
 - if we have this point in hashmap, we need to check if we have 2 points with appropriate coordinates to make a square:

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7da9d4ce-2e14-41c9-aa81-db87ac737c88_1692965951.3181722.png)
 - Than we update res variable by multiplying number of occurences of three dots.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

