# Intuition
I realized, using the geometry knowledge and constraints in problem will make it easier.
For any point when added, we'll add it once, then we'll increase the counter.
For any query point, we'll find all points for same x, for these 2 points, we'll find squares left side and right side.

# Approach
add: save all points in a plain object. `points[x][y] = count of this same point`
count: find other y values for given x, for each of these points, find distance, if distance is positive find other two points at -d side and +d side, multiply occurances of all 3 points.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Worst case time complexity - O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class DetectSquares {
    points:{[k:number]:{[k:number]:number}}
    constructor() {
        this.points = {}
    }

    add(point: number[]): void {
        const [x,y] = point
        this.points[x] = this.points[x] || {}
        this.points[x][y] = this.points[x][y] || 0
        this.points[x][y]++
    }

    count(point: number[]): number {
        let [gx,gy] = point
        let otherYs = this.points[gx]
        if(!otherYs) return 0
        let s=0
        for(let ey in otherYs){
            let d = Math.abs(Number(ey)-gy)
            if(d<=0) continue
            // find left side square
            if(this.points[gx-d]?.[ey] && this.points[gx-d]?.[gy]) {
               s+=  this.points[gx-d][ey]*this.points[gx-d][gy]*this.points[gx][ey]
            }
            // find right side square
            if(this.points[gx+d]?.[ey] && this.points[gx+d]?.[gy]) {
               s+=  this.points[gx+d][ey]*this.points[gx+d][gy]*this.points[gx][ey]
            }
        }
        return s
    }
}

